					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Roth, I know this can be overwhelming at first. In fact, you can get away with simpler sprite handlers depending on the type of your game.
<br />
<br />What we've been presenting you is very useful in dynamic setups, when a variable number of objects can be active at once, in which case some sort of sprite handler is necessary to cycle them, hide the unused ones and so on.
<br />
<br />If your game is so simple that it allows you to hardcode individual objects to certain OAM locations (should only happen when you have a small constant number of objects on screen), there is no problem with that. Just keep in mind that this is not the standard way to do it (as in "not many commercial games did it"), because it's very limited.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

